<p>An important reason is to add one and only one variable as the "Root" of your namespace...</p>

<pre><code>var MyNamespace = {}
MyNamespace.foo= function() {

}
</code></pre>

<p>or</p>

<pre><code>var MyNamespace = {
  foo: function() {
  },
  ...
}
</code></pre>

<p>There are many techniques for namespacing. It's become more important with the plethora of JavaScript modules available.</p>

<p>Also see <em><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/881515/">How do I declare a namespace in JavaScript?</a></em></p>
